modules.description: Configures backend settings for sending traces, metrics, and logs via OTLP, allowing custom URLs for each signal type, debug mode, batch timeouts, and thread management. Works with strings, lists of headers, integers, and booleans to define endpoint configurations and behavior. Used to set up observability pipelines with specific endpoints and performance parameters.

Provides functions for creating and managing traces, spans, and metrics, with support for exporting data to OpenTelemetry backends. Works with types such as trace IDs, span contexts, and metric values to track application performance and behavior. Used to integrate distributed tracing into server applications and send telemetry data to Jaeger or other OpenTelemetry-compatible collectors.

Configures backend settings for sending telemetry data via OTLP, supporting custom URLs, debug mode, batch timeouts, and thread management. Accepts strings, header lists, integers, and booleans to define endpoint configurations and behavior. Enables setup of observability pipelines with precise control over signal routing and performance. Example: specify a custom metrics endpoint with a 500ms batch timeout and authentication headers.
